text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild]]%0a%0a!Linguistic Discrimination in satire%0a%0a:Author: kevinx%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a''Sorry to Bother You'' is a 2018 satire that examines BVE in the workplace%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aIn 2018's ''Sorry to Bother You'', the main character, Cash, played by Lakeith Stanfield, is advised to adopt a "white voice" in order to get ahead as a telemarketer. Cash is immediately encouraged by his increased success adopting a "white voice" (being literally dubbed by David Cross) and, in acting more "white", is granted a look behind the scenes of the company he works for.%0a%0aTrailer (warning: language and somewhat explicit material):%0ahttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PQKiRpiVRQM%0a%0aCash is given some advice (warning: some language):%0ahttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T5X3cu1B87k%0a%0aIn the scene above, Cash and his colleague speak casually in BVE, replacing fricative [θ] or [ð]s with the alveolar stop [d] in words like ''the'' ([ðə] -> [də]) and using "ain't" instead of "haven't" for negation (as well as double negation) in "I ain't got no white voice". %0a%0aCash at first responds mockingly to his colleague's advice. He mentions that "people say I talk with a white voice anyway", to which his colleague responds that he still doesn't talk "white enough", comparing Cash's speaking to "Will Smith white". His colleague then shows Cash how to speak in a "white voice", what might be considered Standard American English. In being dubbed by an actual white actor, this scene highlights the unrealistic expectation for BVE speakers to speak in Standard American English in order to succeed and be accepted professionally.%0a%0aI chose this example because dark comedy and satire is a great way to shine a light on issues that may be too ingrained or mundane for people not affected. By exaggerating "white voice" in contrast to BVE, ''Sorry to Bother You'' encourages more vivid conversation about BVE discrimination. It's an offbeat movie, but I would definitely recommend checking it out.%0a%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a#foxbegin 210501-064157-24080#%0a(:div1 class=messagehead:)%0a>>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a[-30.04.2021 - 23:41-] &nbsp; %0a>>%3c%3c%0a(:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a>>rfloat%3c%3c%0a{[foxdelrange button 210501-064157-24080 {$FullName} ]}%0a>>%3c%3c%0a(:if1end:)%0a!!!!!Abi_S%0a(:div1end:) %0a>>messageitem%3c%3c %0a'''Applicant names '''%0a>>messageitem%3c%3c%0aI forgot what study this was, but a person got more interviews with a white name than their own original name. %0a>>%3c%3c%0a#foxend 210501-064157-24080#%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: D:)%0a(:Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild:)
